  "response": "Franz Ferdinand was an Archduke of Austria-Este and heir presumptive to the Austro-Hungarian throne. He is most famous for being assassinated on June 28, 1914, in Sarajevo, Bosnia, by Gavrilo Princip, a Bosnian Serb nationalist. This assassination is widely considered the immediate trigger that sparked World War I, as it led to a series of diplomatic tensions and declarations of war between European powers. The event set in motion a chain reaction of alliances and military mobilizations that ultimately resulted in the outbreak of the first global war in modern history.",
